result.execSummary:
The defendant Shaun G. Wallace was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Provide Sex Offender Information, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(2)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to obtain and maintain employment.
Defendant to comply and fulfill all requirements of the Sex Offender Registration Program.   No DNA sample ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another felony conviction.

timeConds.notes: Huber Privileges granted.  No Good Time credit. The Court has no objection to transfer of the sentence provided the Defendant can make the appropriate arrangements.  Remaining balance of sentence to be served forthwith.
